# 01 — UAMI + Azure DevOps Workload Identity Federation

> **Owner: central platform / platform-engineering team.** This creates a
> user-assigned managed identity (UAMI) and federates an Azure DevOps WIF ARM
> service connection to it — **no service principal secret / PAT is created**.

Onboarding path: **{{ONBOARDING_PATH}}** · posture: **{{POSTURE}}** · platform: **Azure DevOps**

## Order of operations
1. Create the UAMI (command below).
2. In Azure DevOps → **Project settings → Service connections → New service
   connection → Azure Resource Manager → Workload Identity federation (manual)**.
   Name it `{{ADO_SERVICE_CONNECTION}}`. On the **manual** configuration screen
   Azure DevOps shows two read-only fields:
   - **Issuer** — click the copy icon and **copy the Issuer value** (an
     `https://vstoken.dev.azure.com/<guid>` URL). Paste it into `--issuer` below.
   - **Subject identifier** — **copy the Subject identifier value**; it has the
     form `{{FED_SUBJECT_ADO}}`. Paste it into `--subject` below.
   Leave the ADO dialog **open** — you finish verifying it after step 3.
3. Add the federated credential to the UAMI using that issuer + subject (below),
   then return to the ADO dialog and click **Verify and save**.

## Commands
```bash
# 1) Create the user-assigned managed identity
az identity create \
  --name {{UAMI_NAME}} \
  --resource-group {{UAMI_RESOURCE_GROUP}} \
  --subscription {{UAMI_SUBSCRIPTION_ID}}

# 3) Federate to the Azure DevOps service connection.
#    Replace <issuer-from-ado-service-connection> with the Issuer shown by ADO.
az identity federated-credential create \
  --name ado-{{ADO_ORG}}-{{ENV_NAME}} \
  --identity-name {{UAMI_NAME}} \
  --resource-group {{UAMI_RESOURCE_GROUP}} \
  --issuer "<issuer-from-ado-service-connection>" \
  --subject "{{FED_SUBJECT_ADO}}" \
  --audiences api://AzureADTokenExchange
```

> Subject identifier format is `sc://<org>/<project>/<service-connection>` — for
> this pilot, `{{FED_SUBJECT_ADO}}`.

## Hand back to the pilot team
- Confirm the service connection `{{ADO_SERVICE_CONNECTION}}` verifies green.
- Grant RBAC next: see `02-rbac-role-assignments.md`.
